comments.content: This could be handwritten. Look a the two different a and t.
The listmaster will come up with alternatives soon (probably).

Thanks for the help. The closest I could find was Brody

[Brody](http://web.archive.org/web/20150315231740/http:/www.linotype.com/88744/brodyregular-font.html)

And yeah, I suspected it might be hand drawn. The "o" i sdifferent too.
